A LITTLE girl was playing at the back of her house on Friday, 24 February when a neighbour snatched her. He then took her to his shack in Oppenheimer Park in Thabong, Free State, where he undressed her and allegedly raped her. ALSO READ: Man shoots and kills ex-girlfriend, daughter As if that's not enough, the man also strangled the eight-year-old. Information was followed up regarding the whereabouts of the 25-year-old neighbour and the community had apprehended him when Thabong police arrived. REGISTER TO COMMENT He was then arrested for rape, while the little girl was taken to Bongani Hospital for medical treatment. According to police spokesman, Captain Stephen Thakeng, the suspect will appear in the Welkom Magistrates Court on Monday, 27 February.  